    initFeature:
      featName: Combat Training
      desc: 'You can choose and take a number of Martial Maneuvers equal to your
        Talent score.<br> By expending one AP you can change your Stance, while fighting
        with a weapon. You choose your first stance at the beginning of the combat.<br>
        - Tree Stance: The default Stance. No additional features. A Stance most
        warriors are taught first.<br> - Waves Stance: If you are holding only one
        weapon and the other hand is free, your main weapon gains one additional
        meter of range. A Stance often used by duelists and rogues.<br> - Earth Stance:
        You lose one AP, but instead gain one Reaction. A defensive Stance focused
        on reacting, rather than attacking.<br> - Flame Stance: You lose one Reaction,
        but instead gain one additional AP. An offensive Stance, that focuses on
        attacking rather than reacting.<br> - Iron Stance: You hold the weapon in
        two hands. Attacks made with this weapon cost one less AP, two less Stamina
        points, and you use a larger damage. A Stance used by noble knights and powerful
        warriors.<br>'
      descOnSheet: By expending one AP you can change your Stance, while fighting
        with a weapon. You choose your first stance at the beginning of the combat.
